Open Redirect is a vulnerability where a web application redirects users to an untrusted external URL based on user-controlled input without proper validation.

                                    
                                                                                        
                                                                                         Parameters to Test
                                                                                         
url, redirect, redirect_uri, redirect_url, redirect_to, redir, rurl, destination, dest, go, to, u,next, next_page, return, returnTo, return_to, return_url, return_path, continue, continue_url, checkout_url,page, page_url, view, view_url, file, file_url, file_name, folder, folder_url, load_url, load_file, img_url, image_url, login_url, turl, link, target, path, del, ink,/redirect/, /cgi-bin/redirect.cgi, /out/, /out?, /login?to=, /go=, /return=, /returnTo=, /return_to=, /continue=, /checkout_url=, /return_path=, /image_url=, /loginto


                                                                                          
                                                                                             Testing Example

https://example.com/login?redirect=https://evil.com


                             
